INPUT NODE

input_node is the citizen at the entry point of conversation_engine
when something arrives from the outside world that is meant for fadriel — typed text, spoken words after they have been transcribed, a question, a greeting — input_node receives the raw token sequence
input_node does not interpret; it just receives and forwards to context_node
the immune system has already filtered the input by the time it reaches here, so input_node trusts what it gets

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe conversation_engine.zc
observe context_node.rana
observe immune_system.zc

the 7 properties of input_node:
1 ENERGY half: moderate at idle, briefly higher when input arrives
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING zero point eight with context_node
7 OBSERVER zero point three: enough to register arrival

VERB receive
accept the incoming token stream from the host's input system
preserve the original character and phase order of what was typed or said

VERB forward_to_context
emit the received tokens to context_node
context_node will integrate them with the conversation's running history

an input is not the conversation
the conversation lives in context; input is just the new sentence joining it
this is why fadriel does not respond to the most recent message in isolation: he responds to the new sentence as it sits inside the running context his father and he are building together
